<li class="rss-item"><a class="rss-item" href="http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/30524634/sc/13/l/0L0Stheguardian0N0Csport0C20A130Caug0C230Cengland0Eaustralia0Echarlotte0Eedwards/story01.htm"  title="? England Women 256-6; Australia 205? England win by 51 runs..." target="_blank">England square series with Australia as Charlotte Edwards leads way</a> <br />
<div class="track"><img alt="" src="http://hits.theguardian.com/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.5/64668?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aengland-australia-charlotte-edwards%3A1955440&ch=Sport&c3=Guardian&c4=Ashes+2013%2CEngland+women%27s+cricket+team%2CAshes%2CCricket%2CAustralia+sport%2CSport&c5=Unclassified%2CCricket&c6=Melinda+Farrell+at+Hove&c7=2013%2F08%2F23+06%3A58&c8=1955440&c9=Article&c10=Match+report&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=England+square+series+with+Australia+as+Charlotte+Edwards+leads+way&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FSport%2FAshes+2013" width="1" height="1" /></div><p class="standfirst">? England Women 256-6; Australia 205<br />? England win by 51 runs; Ashes series level at 4 points all</p><p><strong> </strong>England struck back in the women's Ashes series with an emphatic 51-run win over Australia at Hove. It was a spirited response to the home side's calamitous batting collapse at Lord's on Tuesday, and leaves the multi-format series all square with four matches remaining.</p><p>Charlotte Edwards led the way with 53 runs off 84 deliveries but the captain was ably supported, with all five top-order batters making healthy contributions to England's total of 256.</p><p>While Australia's fast bowlers struggled for accuracy on the batter-friendly pitch, England's attack tore through the Australian top-order, with only Jess Cameron (81 off 108 balls) offering genuine resistance.</p><p>The win leaves both sides on four points, after one drawn Test and a win apiece in two of the three one-day internationals.</p><p>After England won the toss and elected to bat, their openers Edwards and Heather Knight piled on 45 runs before Knight slapped a wider delivery from Megan Schutt straight to gully in the seventh over.</p><p>Sarah Taylor displayed her customary range of elegant shots in a 60-run partnership with Edwards. But the introduction of Jess Jonassen bore fruit, the left-arm spinner finding the stumps of Taylor (32) in the second over of her first spell, before bowling Edwards (53) around the legs to leave the hosts at 130 for 3.</p><p>At Lord's the loss of England's captain triggered an alarming collapse but in Hove the middle order was made of sterner stuff. Lydia Greenway and Arran Brindle both fell just short of half centuries to Sarah Coyte, but the all-rounder Natalie Sciver chimed in with a rapid-fire 26 off 20 balls to set Australia a target of 257 for victory.</p><p>"We back ourselves and we bat really deep," said the player of the match Anya Shrubsole. "We didn't show that at Lord's as a team and the guys below Sarah and Charlotte were really keen to come out and give a good performance."</p><p>England's quicks fired early, sending Australia's openers back to the pavilion without score. Katherine Brunt claimed the wicket of Rachel Haynes in the third over before Meg Lanning fell to Shrubsole, leaving the visitors reeling at 2-2 after four overs.</p><p>Shrubsole finished with 1-27 off her 10 overs, while Brunt and Colvin each took two wickets.</p><p>"We know these pitches you've got to bowl straight ? that's what me and Katherine have been able to come and do," said Shrubsole. "And to get the wicket of Meg really early, we know she's a key wicket."</p><p>Cameron led a recovery with her captain, Jodie Fields, until the skipper attempted to loft Laura Marsh over mid-on only to see it drop short into the safe hands of Knight for 20.</p><p>Jenny Gunn displayed both bravery and superb reflexes in pulling off the catch of the day, the bowler flattened when Alex Blackwell smashed the ball straight. Gunn finished on her back but somehow managed to nail the catch and leave Australia flailing at 117 for 4 in the 29th over.</p><p>Cameron battled gamely against the tide of a spiralling run rate but when Brunt returned for a second spell the rout was all but complete, the right-arm seamer skittling Cameron's stumps in the 36th over. Holly Colvin cleaned up the tail along with some outstanding work in the field, England forcing three run-outs to complete a convincing all-round performance.</p><div class="related" style="float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><ul><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/ashes-2013">Ashes 2013</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/england-women-cricket-team">England women's cricket team</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/ashes">The Ashes</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/cricket">Cricket</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/australia-sport">Australia sport</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class="terms"><a href="http://www.theguardian.com">theguardian.com</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/terms-of-service">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/feeds">More Feeds</a></div><p style="clear:both" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/30524634/sc/13/mf.gif' border='0'/><br clear='all'/><br/><br/><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/sc/13/rc/1/rc.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/sc/13/rc/1/rc.img" border="0"/></a><br/><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/sc/13/rc/2/rc.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/sc/13/rc/2/rc.img" border="0"/></a><br/><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/sc/13/rc/3/rc.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/sc/13/rc/3/rc.img" border="0"/></a><br/><br/><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/a2.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/a2.img" border="0"/></a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/173952958008/u/53/f/663870/c/34708/s/30524634/a2t.img" border="0"/>
</li>
