<li class="rss-item"><a class="rss-item" href="http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/3051fa4d/sc/12/l/0L0Stheguardian0N0Cfootball0C20A130Caug0C230Cpremier0Eleague0Esquad0Esheets0Etottenham0Eswansea/story01.htm"  title="According to André Villas-Boas, &quot;the body is tired but ..." target="_blank">Tottenham v Swansea City: Squad sheets</a> <br />
<div class="track"><img alt="" src="http://hits.theguardian.com/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.5/99106?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Apremier-league-squad-sheets-tottenham-swansea%3A1955434&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Premier+League+%28Football%29%2CTottenham+Hotspur+%28Football%29%2CSwansea+City+%28football+club%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=&c7=2013%2F08%2F23+06%3A35&c8=1955434&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=Squad+sheets+%28football%29&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Tottenham+v+Swansea+City%3A+Squad+sheets&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FPremier+League" width="1" height="1" /></div><p>According to André Villas-Boas, "the body is tired but the mind is happy, absolutely", following Tottenham's <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/2013/aug/22/dinamo-tbilisi-tottenham-hotspur-europa-league" title="">5-0 Europa League thumping of Dinamo Tbilisi</a>, and Swansea are in similar mood. They, too, scored five in the competition, <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/2013/aug/22/swansea-city-petrolul-ploiesti-europa-league" title="">against Petrolul Ploiesti</a>, albeit at home, helping them a little in terms of time not spent travelling. The mission for both clubs is to prove that Europe will not sap them. This fixture was tight last season and Villas-Boas is anticipating more of the same. <strong>David Hytner</strong></p><p><strong>Kick-off </strong>Sunday 4pm<strong> </strong></p><p><strong>Venue</strong> White Hart Lane<strong> </strong></p><p><strong>Last season </strong>Tottenham 1 Swansea 0</p><p><strong>Referee </strong>N Swarbrick</p><p><strong>This season</strong> <strong>G</strong>1, <strong>Y</strong>3, <strong>R</strong>, 3.00 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds</strong> <strong>H</strong> 4-7-1 <strong>A</strong> 9-2 <strong>D</strong> 3-1</p><h2><strong>Tottenham</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Friedel, Gomes, Naughton, Dawson, Fryers, Sandro, Adebayor, Dembélé, Carroll, Assou-Ekotto, Townsend, Defoe</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Assou-Ekotto (abdominal), Adebayor (match fitness)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Holtby (knee, 31 Aug), Bale (foot, Sep)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> WWWDWD</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y0 R0</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Soldado 1</p><h2><strong>Swansea</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Tremmel, Zabret, Amat, Ki, Hernández, Lamah, Monk, Lita, Moore, Taylor, Situ, Pozuelo, Obeng, Richards, Donnelly, De Guzmán</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> None</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Dyer (hamstring, 31 Aug)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> LLLWDL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y0 R0</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Bony 1</p><div class="related" style="float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><ul><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/premierleague">Premier League</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/tottenham-hotspur">Tottenham Hotspur</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/swansea">Swansea City</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class="terms"><a href="http://www.theguardian.com">theguardian.com</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/terms-of-service">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/feeds">More Feeds</a></div><p style="clear:both" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/3051fa4d/sc/12/mf.gif' border='0'/><br clear='all'/>
</li>
<li class="rss-item"><a class="rss-item" href="http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/3051e3d7/sc/12/l/0L0Stheguardian0N0Cfootball0C20A130Caug0C230Cjack0Ewilshere0Earsenal0Earsene0Ewenger/story01.htm"  title="? Midfielder brands critics of Arsenal manager 'ridiculous'?..." target="_blank">Jack Wilshere says he may leave Arsenal if Arsène Wenger departs</a> <br />
<div class="track"><img alt="" src="http://hits.theguardian.com/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.5/47227?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Ajack-wilshere-arsenal-arsene-wenger%3A1955412&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Arsenal+FC+%28Football%29%2CArsene+Wenger%2CJack+Wilshere+%28football%29%2CTransfer+window+%28football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=Press+Association&c7=2013%2F08%2F23+06%3A16&c8=1955412&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Jack+Wilshere+says+he+may+leave+Arsenal+if+Ars%C3%A8ne+Wenger+departs&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FArsenal" width="1" height="1" /></div><p class="standfirst">? Midfielder brands critics of Arsenal manager 'ridiculous'<br />? 'I want to win things but if the boss leaves things could change'</p><p>Jack Wilshere has branded Arsène Wenger's critics "ridiculous" and warned he would have to reconsider his future at Arsenal if the Frenchman were to leave the club.</p><p>Wenger has come under fire for Arsenal's inability to make any significant signings after failing with approaches for Gonzalo Higuaín, Wayne Rooney, Luis Suárez and Luiz Gustavo.</p><p>The fallout from the <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/2013/aug/17/arsenal-aston-villa-premier-league" title="">3-1 defeat by Aston Villa</a> last Saturday saw the <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/2013/aug/19/arsene-wenger-arsenal-ast-contract" title="">Arsenal Supporters' Trust declare it would be "inappropriate" for the board to offer him a new contract</a> until the transfer window closes.</p><p>Wilshere, however, insists that he might be forced to leave the Emirates Stadium were Wenger to depart.</p><p>"I want to win things with Arsenal and I want to be there in the future, but if the boss leaves then things could change," Wilshere told Zapsportz.com.</p><p>"Arsenal are always in my heart and by signing a deal for the next five years [it] shows my commitment to them and their commitment to me, so at the moment everything is good.</p><p>"Arsène Wenger has been there for so many years and he's always delivered trophies. OK, we've had a little dip in the last five or six years, but he's a great manager and people who question his ability are ridiculous.</p><p>"He's qualified for the Champions' League for 16 years so I think he's the right man for the job."</p><div class="related" style="float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><ul><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/arsenal">Arsenal</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/arsene-wenger">Arsène Wenger</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/jack-wilshere">Jack Wilshere</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/transfer-window">Transfer window</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class="terms"><a href="http://www.theguardian.com">theguardian.com</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/terms-of-service">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/feeds">More Feeds</a></div><p style="clear:both" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/3051e3d7/sc/12/mf.gif' border='0'/><br clear='all'/>
</li>
<li class="rss-item"><a class="rss-item" href="http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/3051e3d8/sc/12/l/0L0Stheguardian0N0Cfootball0C20A130Caug0C230Cpremier0Eleague0Esquad0Esheets0Emanchester0Eunited0Echelsea/story01.htm"  title="José Mourinho has suggested Chelsea will make a third bid fo..." target="_blank">Manchester United v Chelsea: Squad sheets</a> <br />
<div class="track"><img alt="" src="http://hits.theguardian.com/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.5/21217?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Apremier-league-squad-sheets-manchester-united-chelsea%3A1955418&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Manchester+United+%28Football%29%2CChelsea+%28Football%29%2CPremier+League+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=&c7=2013%2F08%2F23+06%3A13&c8=1955418&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=Squad+sheets+%28football%29&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Manchester+United+v+Chelsea%3A+Squad+sheets&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FManchester+United" width="1" height="1" /></div><p>José Mourinho has suggested Chelsea will make a third bid for Wayne Rooney following this match, in turn surely affecting David Moyes's thinking in regards to whether or not to select the unhappy striker. Should Rooney be picked from the start it will be interesting to see the reception he receives from a home crowd whose patience has been stretched by the will-he-won't-he-leave saga. <strong>Jamie Jackson</strong></p><p><strong>Kick-off </strong>Monday 8pm<strong> </strong></p><p><strong>Venue</strong> Old Trafford</p><p><strong>Last season </strong>Man Utd 0 Chelsea 1</p><p><strong>Live</strong> Sky Sports 1</p><p><strong>Referee </strong>M Atkinson</p><p><strong>This season</strong> <strong>G</strong>1, <strong>Y</strong>2, <strong>R</strong>0, 2.00 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds</strong> <strong>H</strong> 11-8 <strong>A</strong> 21-10 <strong>D</strong> 11-5</p><h2><strong>Manchester Utd</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Lindegaard, Buttner, F Da Silva, Smalling, Hernández, Giggs, Anderson, Keane, Amos, Zaha, JanuzajRooney, Evans, Young, Nani <strong>Doubtful</strong> Young (ankle), Hernández (hamstring), Nani (groin)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> R Da Silva (hamstring, Sep), Powell (leg, unknown), Fletcher (illness, unknown)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> WDWLDW</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y3 R0</p><p><strong>Leading scorers</strong> Van Persie 2, Welbeck</p><h2><strong>Chelsea</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Hilário, Schwarzer, Lukaku, Bertrand, Azpilicueta, Chalobah, Mikel, Essien, Moses, Van Ginkel, De Bruyne, Ba, Schürrle, McEachran, Hutchinson</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> None</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> David Luiz (hamstring, 31 Aug), Kalas (foot, Dec)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> WWWWDW</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y1 R0</p><p><strong>Leading scorers</strong> Ivanovic, Lampard, Oscar, 1</p><div class="related" style="float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><ul><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/manchester-united">Manchester United</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/chelsea">Chelsea</a></li><li><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/football/premierleague">Premier League</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class="terms"><a href="http://www.theguardian.com">theguardian.com</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/terms-of-service">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/help/feeds">More Feeds</a></div><p style="clear:both" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://feeds.theguardian.com/c/34708/f/663870/s/3051e3d8/sc/12/mf.gif' border='0'/><br clear='all'/>
