<div class="track"><img alt="" src="http://hits.theguardian.com/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.5/77847?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Apremier-league-squad-sheets-stoke-palace%3A1955398&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Premier+League+%28Football%29%2CStoke+City+%28Football%29%2CCrystal+Palace+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=&c7=2013%2F08%2F23+05%3A41&c8=1955398&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=Squad+sheets+%28football%29&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Stoke+City+v+Crystal+Palace%3A+Squad+sheets&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FPremier+League" width="1" height="1" /></div><p>Both teams suffered less-than-surprising defeats in their respective opening day games so will be hoping to use this match to put their first points on the board. In their last meeting Stoke won 4-1, but judging from their showing against Spurs Ian Holloway's men should put up a fight, and could include Jason Puncheon, who has arrived on loan from Southampton. <strong>Sophy Coombes-Roberts</strong></p><p><strong>Kick-off </strong>Saturday 3pm<strong> </strong></p><p><strong>Venue</strong> The Britannia Stadium</p><p><strong>Last season </strong>n/a</p><p><strong>Referee </strong>A Marriner</p><p><strong>This season</strong> <strong>G</strong>1, <strong>Y</strong>5, <strong>R</strong>1, 7.00 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds</strong> <strong>H</strong> 5-6-1 <strong>A</strong> 7-2 <strong>D</strong> 12-5</p><h2><strong>Stoke</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Sorensen, Butland, Muniesa, Wilson, Wilkinson, Shotton, Pennant, Palacios, Edu, Kightly, Jones, Jerome</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> None</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Shea (knee, Sep), Palacios (illness, Sep), Ness (unknown)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> LDLDWW</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y1 R0</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> n/a</p><h2><strong>Crystal Palace</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Alexander, Grandin, Ramage, Campaña, Phillip